Poisson Processes & Exponential Waiting Times
Overview

This project documents my understanding and implementation of Poisson processes, a fundamental stochastic model used in quantitative finance. I focus on both the mathematical foundations and practical simulation techniques used in quant work, market microstructure, and risk modelling.

A Poisson process is used to model events that:

Occur randomly in time

Are independent of previous events

Have a constant average rate Î»

Allow at most one event in an infinitesimally small interval

Have exponential waiting times between events

Understanding these principles is essential for modelling limit order arrivals, price jumps, default events, and other market phenomena.

1. Mathematical Foundations
1.1 Event Probability in a Small Interval

For a small time interval Î”t:

Probability of one event:
P(1 event in Î”t)=Î»Î”t

